==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spur-shell
<hw>Spur"-shell`</hw> <pr>(sp⟦ucir⟧r"sh⟦ecr⟧l`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of several species of handsome marine
gastropod shells of the genus <gen>Trochus</gen>, or
<gen>Imperator</gen>. The shell is conical, with the margin toothed
somewhat like the rowel of a spur.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spurt</ent>⟦br⟧
